.TH "bcm63xx_uninit_udc_hw" 9 "bcm63xx_uninit_udc_hw" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bcm63xx_uninit_udc_hw \- Shut down the hardware prior to driver removal.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" bcm63xx_uninit_udc_hw
.BI "(struct bcm63xx_udc *udc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "udc" 12
Reference to the device controller.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This just masks the IUDMA IRQs and releases the clocks.  It is assumed
that \fBbcm63xx_udc_stop\fP has already run, and the clocks are stopped.
